{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "name": "ClientSide Ecommerce API",
    "description": "Storefront API (2026-05): health, OTP auth, Google OAuth2 + JWT exchange, profile, service area, catalog, storefront cart/checkout/account/orders, **promotions (coupons + live cart pricing)**.\n\n**Cart**\n- Add/update/remove return the **same full cart JSON** (items + summary + promotions).\n- Use **`delta`** (+1 / -1) or **`quantity`** on `POST/PATCH …/cart/items`. Max **99** per line; at qty 1, `delta: -1` → `MINIMUM_QUANTITY` (use DELETE to remove).\n- Optional **`couponCode`** on GET (`?couponCode=`), POST/PATCH/DELETE item bodies. Invalid coupon stays in response as `promotions.coupon.status: not_applicable` with a reason.\n- `GET /storefront/cart` test scripts set `{{cartSubtotalMinor}}` from `summary.subtotal_before_coupon_minor` (or `subtotal_minor`).\n\n**Promotions**\n- List all codes: `GET /storefront/coupons`. Cart shows up to **3** `suggested_coupons`; checkout applies coupon: `POST /storefront/checkout` with `couponCode`.\n- Use folder **Promotions — local test flow** (run in order after auth + address + cart item).\n\n**Tenant / shop**\n- Send **`x-shop-id: {{shopId}}`** on tenant-scoped routes (catalog, storefront, checkout, …). Query parameters **`shopId`** / **`shop_id`** are not read for resolution.\n\n**Setup**\n- `npm run dev` — default **4100**. `npm run db:migrate`. A **shop** row must exist; set **`shopId`** (collection or environment variable).\n- **`.env`:** `DATABASE_URL`, `JWT_SECRET`, `API_PUBLIC_URL`, Google OAuth vars. Redirect URI in Google Console: `{API_PUBLIC_URL}/api/oauth/callback/google`.\n\n**JWT**\n- **`POST /api/auth/otp/verify`** and **`POST /api/auth/oauth/jwt`** return **`accessToken`**.\n- Protected routes: `Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}`.\n\n**Postman + OAuth JWT exchange**\n- Cookie flow: after browser Google callback to `/api/oauth/callback/google`, cookie **`storefront_oauth_exchange`** is set on API host.\n- `POST /api/auth/oauth/jwt` with body `{}` succeeds only when valid cookie is sent.\n\n**Architecture note**\n- Picker/staff APIs are not served by this app anymore; picker notifications are handled by a separate server/process.\n\n**CORS**\n- API allows credentials for **`CORS_ORIGIN`** (e.g. `http://localhost:5173`). OAuth `POST /api/oauth/sign-in/social` may need **`Origin`** matching that value when testing from CLI.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
